{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "x402-gateway-collection",
		"name": "x402 Gateway",
		"description": "Complete Postman collection for the x402 BSV payment gateway.\n\nArchitecture:\n- Gateway: http://localhost:8402 (issues challenges, verifies proofs)\n- Delegator: http://localhost:8403 (adds fee inputs to template transactions)\n- Client orchestrates: Gateway -> Delegator -> (Broadcast) -> Gateway\n\nProtocol Flow (Profile B - Template Mode):\n1. GET /v1/expensive -> 402 + X402-Challenge header\n2. Decode challenge (base64url JSON) -> extract template.rawtx_hex\n3. POST /delegate/x402 with {\"partial_tx\":\"<rawtx_hex>\"} -> {\"completed_tx\":\"<hex>\",\"txid\":\"<hex>\"}\n4. Broadcast completed_tx (skipped in demo mode)\n5. Build X402-Proof header -> base64url encode\n6. GET /v1/expensive with X402-Proof header -> 200 OK\n\nNo BSV crypto library needed. All signing is handled server-side by the gateway and delegator.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "gatewayUrl",
			"value": "http://localhost:8402",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "delegatorUrl",
			"value": "http://localhost:8403",
			"type": "string"
		}
	],
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Health & Status",
			"description": "Health check endpoints for the gateway and delegator services.",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Gateway Health",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/health",
							"host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
							"path": ["health"]
						},
						"description": "Returns gateway health status including pool statistics, network, profile mode, and version."
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Gateway is healthy', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has pool stats', function () {",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('nonce_pool');",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('fee_pool');",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('payment_pool');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has network info', function () {",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('network');",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('profile');",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Delegator Health",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{delegatorUrl}}/health",
							"host": ["{{delegatorUrl}}"],
							"path": ["health"]
						},
						"description": "Returns delegator health status including uptime and pool information."
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Delegator is healthy', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "x402 Protocol Flow (Manual)",
			"description": "Step-by-step x402 payment flow for Profile B (Gateway Template mode).\n\nRun these requests in order:\n1. Unpaid Request - triggers 402, extracts challenge\n2. Call Delegator - decodes challenge in pre-request script, sends template to delegator for fee input addition\n3. Broadcast (placeholder) - skipped in demo mode\n4. Paid Request - builds proof header in pre-request script and accesses protected resource\n\nEach step stores collection variables for the next step via test/pre-request scripts.\n\nPrerequisites:\n- Gateway running on {{gatewayUrl}} with TEMPLATE_MODE=true\n- Delegator running on {{delegatorUrl}}",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Step 1: Unpaid Request (get 402 challenge)",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/v1/expensive",
							"host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
							"path": ["v1", "expensive"]
						},
						"description": "Request the protected resource without payment.\n\nThe gateway responds with:\n- HTTP 402 Payment Required\n- X402-Challenge header (base64url-encoded JSON challenge)\n- X402-Accept header (supported payment schemes)\n\nThe test script extracts the challenge, decodes it, and stores it for subsequent steps."
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Returns 402 Payment Required', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(402);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has X402-Challenge header', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.header('X402-Challenge');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has X402-Accept header', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.header('X402-Accept');",
									"    var accept = pm.response.headers.get('X402-Accept');",
									"    pm.expect(accept).to.eql('bsv-tx-v1');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response body indicates payment required', function () {",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql(402);",
									"    pm.expect(json.code).to.eql('payment_required');",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Extract and store the challenge",
									"var challengeEncoded = pm.response.headers.get('X402-Challenge');",
									"if (challengeEncoded) {",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeEncoded', challengeEncoded);",
									"    console.log('Stored challengeEncoded (' + challengeEncoded.length + ' chars)');",
									"",
									"    // Decode base64url to inspect challenge content",
									"    function base64urlDecode(str) {",
									"        str = str.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/');",
									"        while (str.length % 4) str += '=';",
									"        return atob(str);",
									"    }",
									"",
									"    try {",
									"        var challengeJSON = base64urlDecode(challengeEncoded);",
									"        var challenge = JSON.parse(challengeJSON);",
									"        console.log('Challenge decoded:', JSON.stringify(challenge, null, 2));",
									"        pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeJSON', challengeJSON);",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has version 1', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.v).to.eql('1');",
									"        });",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has scheme bsv-tx-v1', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.scheme).to.eql('bsv-tx-v1');",
									"        });",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has amount_sats', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.amount_sats).to.be.a('number');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.amount_sats).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
									"        });",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has nonce_utxo', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('nonce_utxo');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.nonce_utxo).to.have.property('txid');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.nonce_utxo).to.have.property('vout');",
									"        });",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has template (Profile B)', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('template');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.template).to.have.property('rawtx_hex');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.template).to.have.property('price_sats');",
									"        });",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has request binding fields', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('domain');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('method');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('path');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('req_headers_sha256');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('req_body_sha256');",
									"        });",
									"",
									"        pm.test('Challenge has expiry', function () {",
									"            pm.expect(challenge).to.have.property('expires_at');",
									"            pm.expect(challenge.expires_at).to.be.greaterThan(Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000));",
									"        });",
									"    } catch (e) {",
									"        console.error('Failed to decode challenge:', e.message);",
									"    }",
									"}"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Step 2: Call Delegator (add fee inputs)",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\"partial_tx\":\"{{templateRawtxHex}}\"}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{delegatorUrl}}/delegate/x402",
							"host": ["{{delegatorUrl}}"],
							"path": ["delegate", "x402"]
						},
						"description": "Send the template transaction from the challenge to the delegator.\n\nThe pre-request script:\n1. Decodes the challenge from Step 1 (base64url -> JSON)\n2. Extracts template.rawtx_hex and stores it as templateRawtxHex\n3. Stores all challenge binding fields for proof building in Step 4\n4. Computes the challenge SHA-256 hash for proof binding\n\nThe delegator:\n1. Parses the partial transaction\n2. Validates structure (nonce input, payee output)\n3. Adds fee inputs from its UTXO pool\n4. Signs the fee inputs\n5. Returns the completed transaction and txid"
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "prerequest",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Decode the challenge from Step 1",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"var challengeEncoded = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeEncoded');",
									"if (!challengeEncoded) {",
									"    throw new Error('No challengeEncoded found. Run Step 1 first.');",
									"}",
									"",
									"function base64urlDecode(str) {",
									"    str = str.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/');",
									"    while (str.length % 4) str += '=';",
									"    return atob(str);",
									"}",
									"",
									"var challengeJSON = base64urlDecode(challengeEncoded);",
									"var challenge = JSON.parse(challengeJSON);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeJSON', challengeJSON);",
									"console.log('Challenge decoded. amount_sats:', challenge.amount_sats);",
									"",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Store challenge binding fields for proof (Step 4)",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeDomain', challenge.domain);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeMethod', challenge.method);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengePath', challenge.path);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeQuery', challenge.query || '');",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeReqHeadersSha256', challenge.req_headers_sha256);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeReqBodySha256', challenge.req_body_sha256);",
									"",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Extract template rawtx_hex for the delegator request body",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"if (!challenge.template || !challenge.template.rawtx_hex) {",
									"    throw new Error('No template in challenge. Gateway must run with TEMPLATE_MODE=true (Profile B).');",
									"}",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('templateRawtxHex', challenge.template.rawtx_hex);",
									"console.log('Template rawtx_hex extracted (' + challenge.template.rawtx_hex.length + ' hex chars)');",
									"console.log('Template price_sats:', challenge.template.price_sats);",
									"",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Compute challenge SHA-256 for proof binding",
									"// Uses CryptoJS (built into Postman sandbox)",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"var challengeHash = CryptoJS.SHA256(challengeJSON).toString();",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeSha256', challengeHash);",
									"console.log('Challenge SHA-256:', challengeHash);"
								]
							}
						},
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Delegator returns 200 OK', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"var json = pm.response.json();",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has completed_tx', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('completed_tx');",
									"    pm.expect(json.completed_tx).to.be.a('string');",
									"    pm.expect(json.completed_tx.length).to.be.greaterThan(0);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has valid txid (64 hex chars)', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('txid');",
									"    pm.expect(json.txid).to.be.a('string');",
									"    pm.expect(json.txid).to.have.lengthOf(64);",
									"    pm.expect(json.txid).to.match(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('completed_tx is valid hex', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(json.completed_tx).to.match(/^[0-9a-f]+$/);",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Store completed transaction and txid for proof building",
									"if (json.completed_tx) {",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('completedTxHex', json.completed_tx);",
									"    console.log('Stored completedTxHex (' + json.completed_tx.length + ' hex chars)');",
									"}",
									"if (json.txid) {",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('txid', json.txid);",
									"    console.log('Stored txid:', json.txid);",
									"}"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Step 3: Broadcast (placeholder - skipped in demo)",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/health",
							"host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
							"path": ["health"]
						},
						"description": "PLACEHOLDER: In production, the client broadcasts the completed_tx to the BSV network.\n\nIn demo mode (BROADCASTER=mock), this step is skipped because the mock broadcaster automatically accepts all transactions. The delegator already handled broadcast internally.\n\nThis request hits /health as a no-op to keep the step numbering consistent.\n\nFor production, you would POST the completedTxHex to a BSV node or use the WhatsOnChain API:\n  POST https://api.whatsonchain.com/v1/bsv/{network}/tx/raw\n  Body: {\"txhex\": \"<completedTxHex>\"}"
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Broadcast step placeholder', function () {",
									"    // In demo mode, the mock broadcaster auto-accepts transactions.",
									"    // In production, POST completedTxHex to a BSV node or API.",
									"    var completedTxHex = pm.collectionVariables.get('completedTxHex');",
									"    var txid = pm.collectionVariables.get('txid');",
									"    console.log('--- Broadcast Summary ---');",
									"    console.log('txid:', txid);",
									"    console.log('completed_tx length:', completedTxHex ? completedTxHex.length + ' hex chars' : 'N/A');",
									"    console.log('In demo mode: broadcast is handled by MockBroadcaster');",
									"    pm.expect(completedTxHex).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"    pm.expect(txid).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Step 4: Paid Request (submit proof)",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "X402-Proof",
								"value": "{{proofHeader}}"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/v1/expensive",
							"host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
							"path": ["v1", "expensive"]
						},
						"description": "Submit the payment proof to access the protected resource.\n\nThe pre-request script builds the X402-Proof header from:\n- completed_tx (hex -> base64 for rawtx_b64 field)\n- txid from the delegator response\n- challenge_sha256 computed from the original challenge JSON\n- Request binding fields from the original challenge\n\nThe proof is a base64url-encoded JSON object:\n{\n  \"v\": \"1\",\n  \"scheme\": \"bsv-tx-v1\",\n  \"txid\": \"<64-char hex>\",\n  \"rawtx_b64\": \"<base64 of completed tx bytes>\",\n  \"challenge_sha256\": \"<64-char hex>\",\n  \"request\": {\n    \"domain\": \"localhost:8402\",\n    \"method\": \"GET\",\n    \"path\": \"/v1/expensive\",\n    \"query\": \"\",\n    \"req_headers_sha256\": \"<hex>\",\n    \"req_body_sha256\": \"<hex>\"\n  }\n}"
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "prerequest",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Gather stored variables from Steps 1 and 2",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"var completedTxHex = pm.collectionVariables.get('completedTxHex');",
									"var txid = pm.collectionVariables.get('txid');",
									"var challengeSha256 = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeSha256');",
									"var challengeDomain = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeDomain');",
									"var challengeMethod = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeMethod');",
									"var challengePath = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengePath');",
									"var challengeQuery = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeQuery');",
									"var challengeReqHeadersSha256 = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeReqHeadersSha256');",
									"var challengeReqBodySha256 = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeReqBodySha256');",
									"",
									"if (!completedTxHex || !txid || !challengeSha256) {",
									"    throw new Error('Missing required variables. Run Steps 1 and 2 first.');",
									"}",
									"",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Helper: convert hex string to standard base64",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"function hexToBase64(hex) {",
									"    var bytes = [];",
									"    for (var i = 0; i < hex.length; i += 2) {",
									"        bytes.push(parseInt(hex.substr(i, 2), 16));",
									"    }",
									"    return btoa(String.fromCharCode.apply(null, bytes));",
									"}",
									"",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Helper: encode string to base64url (no padding)",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"function base64urlEncode(str) {",
									"    return btoa(str).replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_').replace(/=+$/g, '');",
									"}",
									"",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"// Build the X402-Proof object per protocol spec",
									"// -------------------------------------------------------",
									"var rawtxB64 = hexToBase64(completedTxHex);",
									"",
									"var proof = {",
									"    v: '1',",
									"    scheme: 'bsv-tx-v1',",
									"    txid: txid,",
									"    rawtx_b64: rawtxB64,",
									"    challenge_sha256: challengeSha256,",
									"    request: {",
									"        domain: challengeDomain,",
									"        method: challengeMethod,",
									"        path: challengePath,",
									"        query: challengeQuery || '',",
									"        req_headers_sha256: challengeReqHeadersSha256,",
									"        req_body_sha256: challengeReqBodySha256",
									"    }",
									"};",
									"",
									"console.log('Proof object:', JSON.stringify(proof, null, 2));",
									"",
									"// Base64url encode the proof JSON for the header",
									"var proofJson = JSON.stringify(proof);",
									"var proofEncoded = base64urlEncode(proofJson);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('proofHeader', proofEncoded);",
									"console.log('X402-Proof header set (' + proofEncoded.length + ' chars)');"
								]
							}
						},
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Returns 200 OK (payment accepted)', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has protected data', function () {",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('data');",
									"    pm.expect(json.data).to.include('100 satoshis');",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('timestamp');",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('path');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has X402-Receipt header', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.header('X402-Receipt');",
									"    var receipt = pm.response.headers.get('X402-Receipt');",
									"    pm.expect(receipt).to.match(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has X402-Status accepted', function () {",
									"    var status = pm.response.headers.get('X402-Status');",
									"    if (status) {",
									"        pm.expect(status).to.eql('accepted');",
									"    }",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has receipt timestamp', function () {",
									"    var receiptTime = pm.response.headers.get('X402-Receipt-Time');",
									"    if (receiptTime) {",
									"        pm.expect(receiptTime).to.be.a('string');",
									"    }",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log('=== x402 payment flow completed successfully! ===');",
									"console.log('Receipt:', pm.response.headers.get('X402-Receipt'));",
									"console.log('Status:', pm.response.headers.get('X402-Status'));"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "x402 Automatic Flow",
			"description": "Automated end-to-end x402 payment flow using Postman Collection Runner.\n\nUse the Collection Runner to execute this folder. Each request uses postman.setNextRequest() to chain to the next step automatically.\n\nFlow: Trigger 402 -> Delegate Transaction -> Build Proof & Pay -> Done\n\nTo run: Select this folder in Collection Runner and click 'Run'.",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Auto 1: Trigger 402 Challenge",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/v1/expensive",
							"host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
							"path": ["v1", "expensive"]
						},
						"description": "Step 1 of the automatic flow. Requests the protected resource without payment, extracts the 402 challenge, decodes it, and chains to the delegator call."
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Returns 402 Payment Required', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(402);",
									"});",
									"",
									"// Extract challenge header",
									"var challengeEncoded = pm.response.headers.get('X402-Challenge');",
									"pm.expect(challengeEncoded).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeEncoded', challengeEncoded);",
									"",
									"// Decode challenge (base64url -> JSON)",
									"function base64urlDecode(str) {",
									"    str = str.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/');",
									"    while (str.length % 4) str += '=';",
									"    return atob(str);",
									"}",
									"",
									"var challengeJSON = base64urlDecode(challengeEncoded);",
									"var challenge = JSON.parse(challengeJSON);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeJSON', challengeJSON);",
									"",
									"// Store challenge binding fields for proof",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeDomain', challenge.domain);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeMethod', challenge.method);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengePath', challenge.path);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeQuery', challenge.query || '');",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeReqHeadersSha256', challenge.req_headers_sha256);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeReqBodySha256', challenge.req_body_sha256);",
									"",
									"// Extract template rawtx_hex",
									"pm.expect(challenge.template).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"pm.expect(challenge.template.rawtx_hex).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('templateRawtxHex', challenge.template.rawtx_hex);",
									"",
									"// Compute challenge SHA-256 hash",
									"var challengeHash = CryptoJS.SHA256(challengeJSON).toString();",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('challengeSha256', challengeHash);",
									"",
									"console.log('Auto 1: Challenge extracted, amount_sats:', challenge.amount_sats);",
									"console.log('Auto 1: Chaining to delegator...');",
									"postman.setNextRequest('Auto 2: Delegate Transaction');"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Auto 2: Delegate Transaction",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\"partial_tx\":\"{{templateRawtxHex}}\"}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{delegatorUrl}}/delegate/x402",
							"host": ["{{delegatorUrl}}"],
							"path": ["delegate", "x402"]
						},
						"description": "Step 2 of the automatic flow. Sends the template transaction to the delegator for fee input addition and signing."
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "prerequest",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"var templateRawtxHex = pm.collectionVariables.get('templateRawtxHex');",
									"if (!templateRawtxHex) {",
									"    throw new Error('No templateRawtxHex. Auto flow must start from Auto 1.');",
									"}"
								]
							}
						},
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Delegator returns 200 OK', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"var json = pm.response.json();",
									"pm.expect(json.completed_tx).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"pm.expect(json.txid).to.not.be.undefined;",
									"",
									"// Store for proof building",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('completedTxHex', json.completed_tx);",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('txid', json.txid);",
									"",
									"console.log('Auto 2: Delegation complete, txid:', json.txid);",
									"console.log('Auto 2: Chaining to paid request...');",
									"postman.setNextRequest('Auto 3: Submit Proof & Access Resource');"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				},
				{
					"name": "Auto 3: Submit Proof & Access Resource",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "X402-Proof",
								"value": "{{proofHeader}}"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{gatewayUrl}}/v1/expensive",
							"host": ["{{gatewayUrl}}"],
							"path": ["v1", "expensive"]
						},
						"description": "Step 3 (final) of the automatic flow. Builds the X402-Proof header from stored variables and submits it to access the protected resource."
					},
					"response": [],
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "prerequest",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"// Gather variables from previous auto steps",
									"var completedTxHex = pm.collectionVariables.get('completedTxHex');",
									"var txid = pm.collectionVariables.get('txid');",
									"var challengeSha256 = pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeSha256');",
									"",
									"if (!completedTxHex || !txid || !challengeSha256) {",
									"    throw new Error('Missing variables. Auto flow must start from Auto 1.');",
									"}",
									"",
									"// Convert hex to base64",
									"function hexToBase64(hex) {",
									"    var bytes = [];",
									"    for (var i = 0; i < hex.length; i += 2) {",
									"        bytes.push(parseInt(hex.substr(i, 2), 16));",
									"    }",
									"    return btoa(String.fromCharCode.apply(null, bytes));",
									"}",
									"",
									"// Encode base64url (no padding)",
									"function base64urlEncode(str) {",
									"    return btoa(str).replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_').replace(/=+$/g, '');",
									"}",
									"",
									"// Build proof object",
									"var proof = {",
									"    v: '1',",
									"    scheme: 'bsv-tx-v1',",
									"    txid: txid,",
									"    rawtx_b64: hexToBase64(completedTxHex),",
									"    challenge_sha256: challengeSha256,",
									"    request: {",
									"        domain: pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeDomain'),",
									"        method: pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeMethod'),",
									"        path: pm.collectionVariables.get('challengePath'),",
									"        query: pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeQuery') || '',",
									"        req_headers_sha256: pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeReqHeadersSha256'),",
									"        req_body_sha256: pm.collectionVariables.get('challengeReqBodySha256')",
									"    }",
									"};",
									"",
									"var proofEncoded = base64urlEncode(JSON.stringify(proof));",
									"pm.collectionVariables.set('proofHeader', proofEncoded);",
									"console.log('Auto 3: Proof header built, submitting payment...');"
								]
							}
						},
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Returns 200 OK (payment accepted)', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has protected data', function () {",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('data');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Has X402-Receipt header', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.header('X402-Receipt');",
									"});",
									"",
									"console.log('=== Auto flow completed successfully! ===');",
									"console.log('Receipt:', pm.response.headers.get('X402-Receipt'));",
									"",
									"// Stop the collection runner",
									"postman.setNextRequest(null);"
								]
							}
						}
					]
				}
			]
		},
